*Special Attack Weapon switch
*[[Teleport to house (tablet)]]
*[[Rune pouch]] with runes for high level alchemy and to hold rune drops
*One or two foods instead of prayer restoring item to have room for drops at beginning of trip
*Rest [[Zamorak brews]] or other prayer restoring item as needed. Ancient and forgotten brews cannot be used with melee because they decrease melee stats. Menaphite remedy can be used to restore stat reductions but is not necessary.
*Zamorak brew increases attack above that of a super combat potion, but less for strength, so super strength potions may be useful to also bring.

===Notes===
*If not using a [[Scythe of vitur]], the recoil damage from a charged [[Ring of suffering (ri)]] ends up dealing more damage than a [[Berserker ring (i)]] would help achieve.
*The [[Scythe of vitur]] may occasionally hit a stray [[Smoke devil]] if one walks underneath the boss. This can cause problems if using the redemption method. 
*The strength bonus from [[Bandos chestplate]] is only worth the extra damage taken if using a scythe; otherwise, armour with high magic defence is recommended for longer trips.
*[[Torva platelegs]] usually do not help achieve a damage boost and thus are not worth for most of the kills, although they are recommended to bring for dragon claws' special attack.
*An [[imbued heart]] is recommended to increase Magic level, which consequently increases magic defence.
*Using the [[Resurrect Greater Zombie]] spell will increase your damage output by around ~5%
*Due to quick kill times, [[Death Charge]] can be used in rapid succession to gain more special attack energy
